The paper deals with a computer vision problem of image classification, specifically for partially occluded images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel scheme using subspace decomposition-based estimation (SDBE) for classification, which involves the use of deep learning technologies. Hence, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the construction of class dictionary and occlusion error dictionary, which involves the use of training sets and extra sets of image pairs, respectively. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed scheme on datasets such as Caltech-101 and ILSVRC2012, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR), respectively.
